

1) User Class
- Represents the main user in the system.
- Contains basic user data:
  id, name, email, password, phone, age
- Includes a method called displayInfo() to print user information.



/*
2) Admin Class (Inheritance)
- Admin extends the User class.
- This means Admin inherits all properties and methods from User.
- Adds an additional method:
  manageNotes()




3) Note Class (Association)
- Represents a note in the system.
- Contains:
  id, title, content
  user: User
- Each Note has an author (User).
- Includes a method preview() to return a short part of the content.
*/



4) NoteBook Class (Composition)
- Contains a collection of Note objects.
- The relationship is Composition:
  meaning the Notebook owns the Notes.
  If the Notebook is deleted, its Notes are deleted as well.
- Methods:
  addNote()
  removeNote()




5) Aggregation (User & NoteBook)
- A User can own multiple Notebooks.
- This is an Aggregation relationship:
  Notebooks can exist independently from the User.




6) Association (Note & User)
- Each Note is associated with a User (author).
- This is a simple relationship without strong ownership.




7) Generic Class - Storage<T>
- A generic class that can store any type of data.
- Methods:
  addItem()
  removeItem()
  getAllItems()


Relationships Summary:

- Inheritance:
  Admin --> User

- Composition:
  NoteBook --> Note

- Aggregation:
  User --> NoteBook

- Association:
  Note --> User
